5:
Sheesh, what a mess. Another
exploded experiment, I'm assuming?
13: Hold on a second... There's no debris.
16: So this is just... a regular old mess?
20:
No, er, this is just... You see, I have
this big report due soon and so I've
been too focused on my work to
notice any sort of mess you speak of.
23:
Although you'd sure be doing me a
solid by helping me clean all this up
though... Just kidding. Unless...
26:
I feel like you've actually started to
regress since we first met.
30:
N-not at all! I j-just learned how to
depend on others, remember? This
is character development!
33:
What kind of character arc is this
supposed to be?!
36:
I can't be there to clean up your
messes every time, you know.
41:
No, Alk! I'd be totally helpless here 
without you!
45:
Oh, I totally forgot! I still need to pay
you back, right?
47:
Planning a trip to the Kaleidoscope
anytime soon? You'll need an
intelligent and charming professor
to lead the way, right?
51:
See? This way both parties win.
Right? 
...Right?
57:
...And so joining us today will be
Professor Nicola.
61:
I mean, I'm good with that, but why
now all of a sudden?
65:
B-because you'll need my magical
knowledge and, er, guidance along
the way, of course! You know what
they say: knowledge is power! Right?
67:
I'll show you what I can do soon
enough, so let's get a move on!
71:
Yes, yes... You two are the real deal,
aren't you?
73:
Especially you, Nimbus! But if you
could just pay a bit more attention
to your surroundings, you'd get an
A+.
80:
Just a minor thing to
note—occasionally your movements
clash with Alk's.
84:
Yeah, well, I've been fightin' on my
own for a long time now. Old habits
die hard.
87:
Oh, of course! No need to change
immediately, but just even having
that awareness in the back of your
mind can make a huge difference!
90:
And you, Alk, should be more loose
with your movement!
92:
It's important to follow others in the
flow of battle, but if you're too rigid
in your movement you'll never reach
your full potential.
100:
Right! Sometimes it's best to let
others take charge—just like me!
104: Um, okay! If you say so!
108:
Wonderful! You two truly are
impressive—you were able to adapt
to my advice almost immediately!
112:
Nah, that could've been better. Let's
try a few more formations.
117:
You got it! I'll move to the front line
this time.
121:
Is it just me, or were both of you
looking a lot more in sync today?
124: No, yeah, I think I felt it too!
128:
Hehe. You two both get an A+ for
your efforts today!
130:
You two learned something
worthwhile, and more importantly, 
I was once again able to maintain
my image!
137:
It hasn't even been a week! What
the heck happened here?!
145:
Yeah, well... I guess I should've seen
this coming.
149:
Um... Since you're here, do you think
you could...
152:
Yeah, yeah. You've still got work to
do, don't you? Let me handle the
cleaning.
167:
Well, thanks to your help, I actually
managed to get it done early!
171:
And whoa! I... I can actually see the
floor again!
175:
Yup. Cleaning's basically done. 
I've made some food for you too!
180: What did I ever do to deserve you?
184: I mean, it's just a snack.
188: You're an angel, Alk. Thank you.
191:
Ah, I wish you'd come and cook for
me every day...
194:
Yeah, I know. But you'd better finish
up soon if you want to get your work
done on time.
200:
Just remember, Alk... My office hours
are always open for you!
